PASS 1 — criterion T8 (LLM/prompt structural-completeness probe, OVERLAY): NOT APPLICABLE / no findings.

T8 is an overlay that only fires when the plan defines an LLM/agent system (prompts, sub-agents, reviewers, LLM output schemas, value-vocabulary enums, or LLM decision/processing protocols). This epic defines none of those. Its artifacts are:
- a single-source-of-truth *snapshot-entry schema* — a data-shape contract for real Jira REST payloads (`comment`/`comments`/`issuelinks`), not an LLM output schema or enum vocabulary;
- sub-op *telemetry counters* (`links_applied`/`comments_applied`/`labels_applied`) — runtime mutation telemetry on the batch-applier outcome, not agent state increments inside a prompt/decision protocol;
- the anti-change-detector guardrail — a documented testing-practice artifact, not an LLM processing protocol.

Because the overlay's precondition is unmet, there are no T8 enum/protocol/counter-placement/fallback/instruction-locality gaps to surface, and no T8 criteria to affirm. This is a clean (empty) result for T8 — recorded here only so the scoping decision is grounded for later passes.
